					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A kabbalistic commentary on the daily prayers.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="50v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sidur ha-Ar"i</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">סדור האר"י</title>
							<note>
								<p>The order of prayers (shaḥarit for week-days, followed by some other portions), with kaṿanot by Isaac Luria.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/120700932">Luria, Isaac ben Solomon, 1534-1572</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/120700932">לוריא, יצחק (האר"י)</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>50 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>190</height>
										<width>125</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>120</height>
										<width>95</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>50 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). Folio 1 is a flyleaf.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Original Hebrew folation.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="16" writtenLines="16">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible ink ruling.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every page.</p>
									<p>Headings, initial words and divine names in bold square characters.</p>
									<p>Additions and comments in the margin.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian square and cursive script of the 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 2 is a title-page.</p>
							<p>Folios 49v-50r taken by someone's attempts to exercise Latin script.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Kavvanoth Hat-Tephilloth. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,015.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
